BFN 

  [Text] Russian Economics Minister Aleksandr Shokhin claims 
the number of taxes will be cut down in Russia soon, the 
taxation system will become simpler while the tax burden will be 
reduced by 20 percent on the average. At the same time, 
according to him, financial discipline will be stepped up. The 
vice premier said the government plans to postpone temporarily 
the payment of VAT on imported equipment to speed up its import 
in Russia. He noted that the State Duma is prepared to back 
this decision, RIA reports. 

